author: TNN
description: In a tragic incident, nine-year-old Prachi Kumawat, a Class 4 student in Sikar district, passed away at school due to a suspected heart attack. During lunch break, she collapsed while opening her tiffin box. Despite immediate medical attention and CPR at a local hospital, she was referred to a larger hospital in Sikar, but was declared dead on arrival.
title: 9-year-old girl dies of suspected heart attack; fainted while having lunch at school

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: President Trump unveiled $92 billion in energy and infrastructure deals to support Big Tech's AI electricity demands, emphasizing the need to surpass China in AI development. Google pledged $25 billion for AI-ready data centers and hydropower modernization, while Blackstone committed over $25 billion to data centers and energy infrastructure.
title: AI race heats up: Donald Trump to voters; ‘We’re way ahead of China'

author: ASHOK PRADHAN AND RIYAN RAMANATH V
description: A college student in Odisha died after allegedly being coerced by her principal to withdraw a sexual harassment complaint. Prior to setting herself ablaze, she was allegedly pressured to apologize to the accused faculty member. The incident sparked public outrage, leading to protests and political clashes.
title: Balasore girl killed self after being forced to apologise to harasser, drop plaint - Kin

author: TNN
description: The Election Commission (EC) is set to share details of approximately 3.57 million Bihar electors, constituting 4.5% of the state's electorate, who were not found at their registered addresses during mandatory visits. This information will be provided to political parties' district presidents and booth level agents for verification by July 25.
title: Election Commission's Bihar drive doesn't find 35.7 lakh voters at their addresses

author: TNN
description: Amritpal Singh Dhillon, a Canada-returned man, was arrested for fatally hitting 114-year-old marathoner Fauja Singh with a borrowed Fortuner on the Jalandhar-Pathankot highway. Dhillon, who fled the scene, claimed he was unaware of who he had struck and was scared. Police investigations, including CCTV footage analysis, led to his arrest, and he now faces culpable homicide and rash driving charges.
title: Hit and run case: 'Didn't know I hit Fauja Singh', says driver held for his death

author: TNN
description: The family of the Yemeni man murdered by Nimisha Priya, an Indian nurse sentenced to death, has firmly rejected any possibility of pardon or blood money. Despite efforts by Indian authorities and religious leaders to negotiate, the victim's brother insists on retribution.
title: Kin of murdered Yemeni refuse pardon for Nimisha Priya

author: TNN
description: A parliamentary panel has suggested time-bound resolution of tax litigations as part of its 285 recommendations on the Income Tax Bill, 2025. The bill, aimed at simplifying and modernizing tax laws, has been examined by a Lok Sabha select committee.
title: Parliamentary panel on I-T Bill backs time-bound resolution of tax cases
